related_items.title: Street scenes, mosques, archaeological sites, and portraits of people in Algeria and Tunisia
description: 81 photographic prints : albumen ; 28 x  36 cm. or smaller. | Predominantly photographs of Algeria including Byzantine and Roman ruins in Tébessa and Thamugadi; mosques, shrines, public buildings, palaces, and street scenes in Mostaganem, Biskra, Algiers, Tlemcen, Constantine, Oran, and Sidi Bel Abbès; and the cathedral at Carthage. Portraits of Algerian people include Berbers, Ouled Naïl women, and prisoners in Annaba. Tunisian views include mosques, buildings, and street scenes in Tunis.

related_items.title: Paul Kruger's arrival in France, November 1900
description: 18 halftone photomechanical prints ; 9 x 14 cm. | Set of post cards reproduced from photographs show the the arrival of President Paul Kruger of the Transvaal, South Africa at Marseilles, France on November 22, 1900. Include views of the ship "Le Guelderland" and views of Kruger leaving the boat; views of the harbor with flags; crowds and waiting press corps. Includes views of Kruger getting into an automobile and views of Kruger's arrival in Paris on November 27, 1900 in front of the Hotel de Ville. Also includes one view with hand-colored portrait of Kruger and the flag of Transvaal.

related_items.title: Archaeological sites and buildings in the Middle East
description: 56 photographic prints ; 28 x 35 cm. or smaller. | Most of photographs were taken by unidentified photographers except for three images (movie stills) of a water wheel, a man plowing, and a boat on the Nile by Fred Niblo and an aerial view of Jerusalem by Frank Mason Good. Most of other images depict sites in North Africa including Egypt (Philae, Abū Sunbul, Luxor, Cairo, and the pyramids at Jīzah); Algeria (Algiers, Oran, Phillipville, and Biskra); Tunis, Tunisia; and Tripoli, Libya. Also includes photographs of Lebanon including the ruins at Baʻlabakk, the Dog River bridge and an aerial view of Zaḥlah; Jerusalem; a tourist tent camp in Palestine; the Ciraǧan Palace  and aerial views of İstanbul; and several museum objects including an Egyptian stele at the Louvre, an Assyrian winged figure at the British Museum and the Sarcophagus of Alexander the Great at the Imperial Ottoman Museum, İstanbul. Includes one photomechanical print of Beduoin men.
